# Example .env for a hybrid kernel: cloud Anthropic for the kernel
# HTTP API (strict-schema NL-gen, clustering judge, approver),
# self-hosted LMS for the M5 / τ³ dev-script improvement loop.
#
# Why hybrid: as of 2026-05, the strongest available local proposers
# (`qwen/qwen3.6-35b-a3b`, `qwen/qwen3-coder-30b`) reliably violate
# strict pydantic schemas like `WorkflowSpec` even with the retry-on-
# validation-error loop enabled — they hold onto training priors like
# `schema_version: "1.1"` that the system prompt explicitly forbids.
# The cheaper bulk-work surfaces (M5 loop driver, τ³ retail loop) are
# τ³-validated against the same models (val_score=0.825).
#
# Pattern: cloud the rare-but-strict, local the frequent-but-tolerant.
#
# Today's caveat: `ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL` is global — every
# `AsyncAnthropic` site in the kernel reads it. So you can't pick
# cloud-for-NL-gen AND local-for-clustering-judge through env vars
# alone right now. The split here is HTTP-API-vs-dev-script, which is
# achievable. Per-surface base URL would be a follow-up.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required — runtime
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
OWNEVO_DATABASE_URL=postgresql://ownevo:ownevo@localhost:5432/ownevo

# Real cloud Anthropic key. NL-gen, workflows iteration runner,
# clustering judge, approver, and the loop driver (when called from the
# kernel HTTP path) all route to cloud.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-...

# Leave ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL UNSET so every kernel `AsyncAnthropic`
# defaults to cloud. (Set it to an LMS URL to route everything local —
# see `.env.local-lms.example`.)
# ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-surface model overrides — all unset → cloud defaults
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Cloud defaults are opus 4.7 for the strict surfaces and sonnet 4.6
# for the cache-sensitive ones. Override per-surface only if you want
# a different cloud model (e.g. sonnet 4.6 for NL-gen to halve cost).
# OWNEVO_NL_GEN_MODEL=
# OWNEVO_INSTRUCTION_PROPOSER_MODEL=
# OWNEVO_META_EVAL_MODEL=
# OWNEVO_AGENT_SOLVER_MODEL=
# OWNEVO_CLUSTER_LABEL_MODEL=
# OWNEVO_CLUSTER_JUDGE_MODEL=
# OWNEVO_APPROVER_MODEL=
# OWNEVO_LOOP_MODEL=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Dev-script loop driver → LMS local (the hybrid half)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# These env vars are read ONLY by `apps/kernel/scripts/run_improvement_loop.py`
# and the τ³ runner — separate from the kernel HTTP API. Lets you do
# `python scripts/run_improvement_loop.py ...` against a local model
# without affecting `/api/nl-gen/generate` callers.
#
# τ³-validated all-local pick (TAU3_LOCAL_TESTPLAN.md): qwen3.6-35b-a3b
# on LMS with the froggeric v13 chat template, ctx=65536, JIT off.
OWNEVO_LLM_HOST=192.168.1.50
OWNEVO_LLM_BASE_URL=http://192.168.1.50:1234
OWNEVO_LLM_MODEL=qwen/qwen3.6-35b-a3b
OWNEVO_LLM_API_FORMAT=anthropic
OWNEVO_LLM_API_KEY=local
